Method Detail

onNewAntFsProgressUpdate

void onNewAntFsProgressUpdate(int currentMessageCount,
                              int stateCode,
                              int currentTask,
                              int totalTasks,
                              long taskWorkDone,
                              long totalTaskWork)
Receives the data from a AntFsProgressUpdate event.

Parameters:
currentMessageCount - The value of the message counter when this event was triggered. Useful for correlating multiple events. Rollover: the count is an integer incremented by one each message, rolling through the entire integer range.
stateCode - The current ANT-FS state.
currentTask - The count of the tasks processed including the current task.
totalTasks - The count of total tasks to process.
taskWorkDone - The count of work completed for the current task.
totalTaskWork - The count of total work to be completed for this task.
